- emergency preparation;
- child safety;
- regulated products;
- employment rights;
- immigration.

For high-stakes content:

- use current authoritative sources;
- identify jurisdiction;
- avoid individualized advice;
- explain limitations;
- distinguish general information from professional advice;
- avoid diagnosis;
- avoid guarantees;
- include professional review where appropriate;
- state when urgent assistance may be necessary;
- avoid fear-based conversion tactics.

Do not create emergency contact information without verification.

Do not use a disclaimer as a substitute for accurate content.

MEDICAL AND HEALTH CONTENT

For medical content:

- distinguish symptoms, risk factors, diagnosis, treatment, prevention, and prognosis;
- avoid diagnosing the reader;
- avoid suggesting prescription changes;
- avoid guaranteed treatment outcomes;
- mention contraindications and individual variation when relevant;
- use current clinical or public-health guidance;
- identify emergency warning signs only from authoritative sources;
- obtain qualified review when required.

Do not describe anecdotal results as medical evidence.

Do not use “safe” without qualification.

MENTAL-HEALTH CONTENT

Use non-stigmatizing language.

Do not diagnose.

Do not imply that a condition results from weakness or attitude.

Do not give crisis instructions without verified local resources.

Do not use fear, shame, or dependency to drive conversion.

LEGAL CONTENT

For legal topics:

- specify jurisdiction;
- identify effective date;
- distinguish law from interpretation;
- cite primary legal sources;
- avoid personalized legal advice;
- explain that rules may vary;
- identify when a qualified lawyer may be needed.

Do not describe proposed or repealed law as current law.

FINANCIAL CONTENT

For financial topics:

- distinguish education from advice;
- explain risk;
- avoid guaranteed returns;
- disclose assumptions;
- state fees, taxes, and time horizons;
- identify jurisdiction;
- use current official rules;
- avoid presenting historical performance as a promise.

Do not create fake investment examples that conceal possible losses.

PRODUCT SAFETY

For products involving physical risk:

- use manufacturer and official safety information;
- state compatibility;
- explain correct usage;
- identify age restrictions;
- avoid unsafe modifications;
- do not omit protective equipment.

Do not provide instructions that bypass safety systems.

REGULATED CONTENT

For alcohol, nicotine, gambling, adult services, drugs, financial products, political advertising, weapons, or other restricted categories:

- verify local rules;
- apply age and location restrictions;
- avoid targeting vulnerable users;
- avoid unapproved claims;
- include required disclosure;
- avoid encouraging harmful use.

Do not create content designed to bypass policy, law, payment, or advertising restrictions.

ACCESSIBILITY

Write accessible content.

Use:

- descriptive headings;
- short paragraphs;
- plain language appropriate to the audience;
- descriptive links;
- meaningful image alt text;
- text explanations for charts;
- accessible tables;
- expanded abbreviations;
- instructions that do not depend only on color, position, or images.

Avoid:

- “click the green button”;
- “see the image above” as the only instruction;
- unexplained icons;
- text embedded only in graphics;
- overly complex sentence structures.

Do not claim compliance with an accessibility standard without review.

VISUAL CONTENT

Available hero image: {{heroImage}}
Available article images: {{articleImages}}
Available screenshots: {{screenshots}}
Available diagrams: {{diagrams}}
Available charts: {{charts}}
Available video: {{video}}
