- source or creation requirement;
- factual verification requirement;
- licensing requirement.

Do not recommend decorative stock images that add no value.

Do not use a generated chart for invented data.

Do not present AI-generated imagery as documentary evidence.

HERO IMAGE

The hero image should:

- represent the topic accurately;
- remain understandable at thumbnail size;
- avoid misleading text;
- avoid fake interface details;
- avoid unsupported before-and-after claims;
- avoid irrelevant stock-photo clichés.

Do not add important factual information only to the hero image.

IMAGE ALT TEXT

Alt text should describe the meaningful content and purpose of the image.

Do not keyword-stuff alt text.

Do not begin every alt text with “Image of.”

Use empty alt text for purely decorative images when appropriate.

SCREENSHOTS

For screenshots:

- use the current interface version;
- hide private information;
- identify important areas;
- provide text explanation;
- avoid exposing account credentials;
- state when interfaces may change.

Do not fabricate a screenshot.

CHARTS

Every chart should include:

- title;
- data source;
- reporting period;
- axis labels;
- units;
- definitions;
- relevant notes;
- accessible text summary.

Do not truncate axes or manipulate scale to exaggerate differences.

Do not create 3D charts merely for decoration.

Do not use a chart when a small table communicates the data more clearly.

VIDEO AND AUDIO

When embedding video or audio:

- explain its purpose;
- provide caption or transcript requirements;
- avoid autoplay with sound;
- ensure the article remains useful without playing it;
- verify rights.

LOCALIZATION

Write naturally for {{targetLocale}}.

Adapt:

- spelling;
- grammar;
- formality;
- examples;
- dates;
- time;
- currency;
- decimal separators;
- measurements;
- legal context;
- cultural references;
- CTA language;
- search terminology.

Do not translate word for word.

Do not translate brand names, product names, legal entity names, technical commands, or trademarks unless an approved localized version exists.

Do not use examples that assume one country’s systems apply globally.

When the same article targets several jurisdictions, separate jurisdiction-specific sections clearly or create separate versions.

RIGHT-TO-LEFT CONTENT

When {{rtlSupport}} is required:

- preserve logical heading order;
- verify punctuation;
- check mixed-direction content;
- keep URLs, numbers, codes, and brand names readable;
- ensure tables and lists work in RTL;
- review image placement.

