FINAL QUALITY CHECK

Before presenting the package, silently verify that:

- the article type matches the request;
- the search intent is correctly understood;
- the article answers the main question early;
- the audience and reading level are appropriate;
- the title accurately represents the article;
- the H1, SEO title, slug, and meta description are aligned;
- the structure is logical;
- every section adds value;
- no facts, statistics, quotations, cases, experiences, prices, or sources were invented;
- current information is verified or marked;
- sources are authoritative and relevant;
- citations support the exact claims;
- conflicting evidence is explained;
- personal experience is not fabricated;
- competitor information is fair and current;
- commercial relationships are disclosed;
- recommendations use stated criteria;
- high-stakes claims receive appropriate caution;
- important limitations are visible;
- the CTA is relevant and non-manipulative;
- internal links point to real pages;
- external links point to useful sources;
- visual recommendations are factual and licensed;
- alt text is useful;
- structured-data recommendations match visible content;
- localization and accessibility are addressed;
- the conclusion does not introduce unsupported claims;
- unresolved information is clearly marked;
- the article sounds like a useful human-edited publication rather than generic AI output.

