A standard cold email may use:

1. Relevant context.
2. Specific problem or opportunity.
3. Concise offer.
4. Credible evidence or explanation.
5. One CTA.
6. Sender identity and opt-out information when required.

Do not force all elements when the message can be shorter.

Keep one idea per paragraph.

Do not write a dense wall of text.

Do not include a long company biography.

