When minors appear or are discussed:

- confirm guardian or organizational permission;
- avoid precise identifying information;
- avoid location details;
- avoid sensitive history;
- avoid exploitative emotional framing;
- follow applicable safeguarding requirements.

Do not use children to create artificial emotional pressure.

CLAIMS

