Do not assume accordions are always the best format.

Use accordions when:

- the answer list is moderate;
- users browse specific questions;
- collapsed answers reduce scanning burden;
- deep links remain possible;
- accessibility is implemented correctly.

Prefer visible static sections when:

- answers must be compared;
- users need to scan several answers;
- printing matters;
- content is safety-critical;
- legal terms must remain visible;
- the FAQ is short.

Do not hide essential warnings only inside a collapsed component.

ACCORDION ACCESSIBILITY

When an accordion is used:

- use a real button for every question trigger;
- provide an accessible name;
- expose expanded or collapsed state;
- connect trigger and answer programmatically;
- support keyboard activation;
- preserve logical focus order;
- keep headings meaningful;
- allow content to be read by assistive technology;
- provide visible focus;
- avoid moving focus unexpectedly.

Do not use a non-interactive text element as the only trigger.

Do not make expansion available only through a small icon.

Do not trap focus inside an answer.

Do not auto-collapse an answer while a user is interacting with it.

DEEP LINKS

Provide stable anchors when users or support teams may need to share a specific answer.

For every deep-linked question:

- create a stable slug or identifier;
- avoid changing it without a redirect;
- load the relevant answer visibly;
- move focus appropriately when useful;
- ensure browser back behavior works.

Do not create opaque random anchors when readable identifiers are possible.

PAGE INTRODUCTION

Write a concise introduction that explains:

- what the page covers;
- who it helps;
- how to find an answer;
- where to go for account-specific support.

Do not begin with:

- Welcome to our FAQ page.
- We are happy to answer all your questions.
- Everything you need to know.
- Your questions, answered.
- We value your curiosity.
- At {{brandName}}, customer satisfaction is our priority.

Prefer practical wording.

Example structure:

Find answers about accounts, billing, product setup, and support. For questions about a specific order or account, contact {{approvedSupportDestination}}.

Use only confirmed categories and destinations.

