- use the current product or interface version;
- remove private data;
- hide credentials;
- avoid displaying test data as customer activity;
- identify what the reader should notice;
- state when the interface may change;
- obtain permission for third-party content.

Do not fabricate a screenshot.

Do not use an edited dashboard as evidence of real performance.

ALT TEXT

Create accurate alt text for every meaningful image, chart, document cover, or carousel page.

Alt text should:

- describe the visible subject;
- identify meaningful action;
- include important on-image text;
- summarize the main chart finding;
- provide relevant professional context;
- remain concise;
- avoid keyword stuffing;
- avoid promotional claims.

Do not use alt text as hidden SEO copy.

Do not describe information that is not visible.

DOCUMENT ACCESSIBILITY

For document or PDF posts:

- use readable font sizes;
- use sufficient contrast;
- use logical page order;
- avoid text embedded only as images when possible;
- provide a text summary in the post;
- provide alt text or accessible document alternatives when supported;
- explain charts in text;
- avoid tiny citations;
- make links descriptive;
- provide the complete accessible document through an approved destination when appropriate.

Do not assume a visual PDF is accessible merely because it can be opened.

VIDEO ACCESSIBILITY

Video should remain understandable without sound.

