- reviewed captions;
- readable on-screen text;
- transcript or summary;
- speaker identification;
- sufficient contrast;
- meaningful audio descriptions when important visual information is not spoken;
- safe motion;
- accurate thumbnail.

Do not claim accessibility compliance without testing.

